SENATE RESOLUTION 396
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to honor Michael Odom upon being named a
2025–2026 Tennessee Distinguished Service
Award winner.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this legislative body should recognize those
individuals who, through their dedication and professional excellence, have made significant
contributions to their communities and to the State of Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, one such individual is Michael Odom, who has been honored as a 2025–
2026 Tennessee Distinguished Service Award winner by the Tennessee Secondary School
Athletic Association in recognition of his outstanding service to high school athletics and
journalism; and
WHEREAS, a native of Jackson and a graduate of North Side High School, Mr. Odom
discovered his passion for storytelling during his collegiate years and pursued a career in
journalism grounded in a deep care for people and the stories they have to tell; and
WHEREAS, Michael Odom began his career in a supporting role at the Jackson Sun,
where he answered phones, recorded box scores, and ensured that the accomplishments of
young athletes were properly recognized, before advancing to become a high school sports
coverage coordinator; and
WHEREAS, over the course of more than two decades, he has distinguished himself as
a respected sports journalist, currently serving as sports editor of the Milan Mirror-Exchange,
where he continues to cover and celebrate high school athletics across West Tennessee
communities, including Brownsville, Fayette, and Lexington; and
WHEREAS, through his work, Mr. Odom has chronicled numerous memorable athletic
moments, including coverage of Spring Fling and events at Middle Tennessee State University's
SR0396
017201
- 1 -

"Glass House," while also demonstrating a unique ability to humanize the athletes whose stories
he tells; and
WHEREAS, Michael Odom has shown a particular gift for capturing the personal
dimensions of sport, as exemplified by his "Faith in Practice" series, which highlights the
intersection of athletics and faith in the lives of student athletes and has had a meaningful
impact on those whose stories he has shared; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Odom's passion for high school sports and his commitment to telling the
stories of Tennessee's young athletes have earned him the respect and admiration of players,
coaches, and communities throughout the region; and
WHEREAS, it is wholly fitting that we specially recognize Michael Odom for his
dedication to excellence in journalism and his invaluable contributions to the coverage of high
school athletics in Tennessee; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor and commend
Michael Odom upon being named a 2025–2026 Tennessee Distinguished Service Award
winner by the Tennessee Secondary School Athletic Association and extend to him our best
wishes for every continued success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
